Sentencas: A novel cell structure for low-temperature SOFC was proposed, using porous stainless steel support substrates combined with thin hydrogen permeable Pd layers, thin-film proton conductor, and thin-film cathode.
Titulo: Development of a novel cell structure for low-temperature SOFC using porous stainless steel support combined with hydrogen permeable Pd layer and thin film proton conductor

Sentencas: Metallic supports consist of sintered ferritic stainless steel spherical powders whose thermal expansion coefficient is close to that of the hydrogen permeable layers and proton conductive electrolytes.
Titulo: Development of a novel cell structure for low-temperature SOFC using porous stainless steel support combined with hydrogen permeable Pd layer and thin film proton conductor

Sentencas: To prepare the cell, both the 1.2-mu m thick proton conductive Sr(Zr0.8Y0.2)O3-delta electrolyte layer and the 100-nm thick (La0.6Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-delta cathode layer were deposited by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) on a Pd-coated porous ferritic stainless steel substrate.
Titulo: Development of a novel cell structure for low-temperature SOFC using porous stainless steel support combined with hydrogen permeable Pd layer and thin film proton conductor

Sentencas: The power generation performance at a low temperature of 400 degrees C was demonstrated in this proposed cell for the first time, while obtained power density is still low and improvements are required.
Titulo: Development of a novel cell structure for low-temperature SOFC using porous stainless steel support combined with hydrogen permeable Pd layer and thin film proton conductor
